-- 2010-10-09T21:06:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-09/france-croatia-win-to-move-to-top-of-qualifying-groups-for-euro-2012.html
France beat Romania 2-0 and Croatia
won 2-1 at Israel to move each atop its group in qualifying for
soccerâ€™s 2012 European Championship.  Second-half substitutes Loic Remy and Yoann Gourcuff scored
in the final seven minutes to give France the win in Paris.
France has six points in Group D, one more than Albania and
Belarus.  Niko Kranjcar scored twice in the first half for Croatia,
before Israel got a goal from Eley Schechter in the 81st minute.
Croatia improves to seven points in Group F, two more than
Georgia and Greece.  The next round of Euro 2012 qualifiers will be played Oct.
